ion accuracies with all eight features (and\nthe four spectroscopically-determined features only) are 93.4% (92.3%) for\nstar-forming galaxies, 69.4% (63.7%) for composite galaxies, 71.8% (67.3%) for\nAGNs, and 65.7% (60.8%) for LINERs. The stacked spectrum of galaxies of the\nsame type as determined by optical diagnostic diagrams at low redshift and RF\nat intermediate redshift are broadly consistent. Our publicly available code\n(https://github.com/zkdtc/MLC_ELGs) and trained models will be instrumental for\nclassifying emission line galaxies in upcoming wide-field spectroscopic\nsurveys.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 19 Aug 2019 19:41:49 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-10-02"}
