 dust particles. Different features\nin the HL Tau disk seem to have different origins. Planet-disk interactions can\nexplain substructure at the external half of the disk, but the internal rings\nseem to be associated to the presence of snow lines of several molecules.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 20 Aug 2019 03:10:42 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 24 Sep 2019 20:05:02 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-10-02"}
