o becomes more difficult (i.e.\nbidirectional to intersecting) and the collision avoidance opportunities\ndecrease (i.e. 80-20 to 50-50 flow ratio). Thus, this paper concludes that the\nmaximum flow rate of pedestrian infrastructures decreases with increasing\ncomplexity.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 20 Aug 2019 08:01:12 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-08-21"}
