 provide explicit formulas for the\ntransformation rules w.r.t. changes the orientation, the several gauges of the\ngiven network, moves and reductions of networks. We show that the image of the\nboundary measurement map and the dimer partition functions do not coincide if\nthe graph is not bipartite.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 20 Aug 2019 15:41:22 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 13 Sep 2019 09:52:29 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 5 Aug 2021 11:41:21 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Fri, 3 Jun 2022 17:23:40 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-06-06"}
